TITLE: Implementing Basic Vert.x HTTP Server Verticle
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a basic Vert.x Verticle that creates an HTTP server listening on port 8080 and responds with a simple HTML message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/site/blog/posts/intro-series/2015-07-14-post-01-my-first-vertx-3-application.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package io.vertx.blog.first;

import io.vertx.core.AbstractVerticle;
import io.vertx.core.Future;

public class MyFirstVerticle extends AbstractVerticle {

  @Override
  public void start(Future<Void> fut) {
    vertx
        .createHttpServer()
        .requestHandler(r -> {
          r.response().end("<h1>Hello from my first " +
              "Vert.x 3 application</h1>");
        })
        .listen(8080, result -> {
          if (result.succeeded()) {
            fut.complete();
          } else {
            fut.fail(result.cause());
          }
        });
  }
}
```

