TITLE: Socket Echo Server with Pause Mechanism
DESCRIPTION: Vert.x Net server that pauses reading when the write queue is full, preventing data loss. However, it doesn't resume reading when the queue drains.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/main/vertx2/vertx1x_docs/docs_md/core_manual_js.md#2025-04-19_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var server = vertx.createNetServer();

server.connectHandler(function(sock) {

    sock.dataHandler(function(buffer) {

        if (!sock.writeQueueFull()) {      
            sock.write(buffer); 
        } else {
            sock.pause();
        }
    });

}).listen(1234, 'localhost');
```

