TITLE: Collecting Complete HTTP Request Body in Vert.x
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to collect the entire HTTP request body by appending each chunk to a buffer and processing it when the request is complete.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/main/vertx2/docs_md/core_manual_ruby.md#2025-04-19_snippet_50

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
server = Vertx::HttpServer.new

server.request_handler do |request|

  # Create a buffer to hold the body
  body = Vertx::Buffer.create(0)

  request.data_handler do |buffer|
    # Append the chunk to the buffer
    body.append_buffer(buffer)
  end

  request.end_handler do
    # The entire body has now been received
    puts "The total body received was #{body.length} bytes"
  end

end.listen(8080, 'localhost')
```

