TITLE: Custom CORS Header Validation Predicate in Vert.x Web Client (Java)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a custom response predicate to validate CORS headers for a pre-flight OPTIONS request in Vert.x Web Client.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/site/blog/posts/2018-12-10-http-response-validation-web-client.md#2025-04-19_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
// Check CORS header allowing to do POST
Function<HttpResponse<Void>, ResponsePredicateResult> methodsPredicate = resp -> {
  String methods = resp.getHeader("Access-Control-Allow-Methods");
  if (methods != null) {
    if (methods.contains("POST")) {
      return ResponsePredicateResult.success();
    }
  }
  return ResponsePredicateResult.failure("Does not work");
};

// Send pre-flight CORS request
client
  .request(HttpMethod.OPTIONS, 8080, "myserver.mycompany.com", "/some-uri")
  .putHeader("Origin", "Server-b.com")
  .putHeader("Access-Control-Request-Method", "POST")
  .expect(methodsPredicate)
  .send(ar -> {
    if (ar.succeeded()) {
      // Process the POST request now
    } else {
      System.out.println("Something went wrong " + ar.cause().getMessage());
    }
  });
```

