TITLE: Using AsyncFile as ReadStream to Upload File via HTTP in Groovy
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use an AsyncFile as a ReadStream to pump data from a file to an HTTP request. It opens a file, creates an HTTP PUT request, and uses a Pump to transfer the file content to the request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/main/vertx2/vertx1x_docs/docs_md/core_manual_groovy.md#2025-04-19_snippet_86

LANGUAGE: groovy
CODE:
```
def client = vertx.createHttpClient(host: "foo.com")

vertx.fileSystem.open("some-file.dat") { ar ->
    if (ar.succeeded) {
        def request = client.put("/uploads") { resp ->
            println "Received response: ${resp.statusCode}"
        }
        def asyncFile = ar.result
        def rs = asyncFile.getReadStream()
        request.chunked = true
        Pump.createPump(rs, request).start()
        rs.endHandler{
            // File sent, end HTTP requuest
            request.end()
        }
    } else {
        log.error("Failed to open file", ar.exception)
    }
}
```

