TITLE: Vert.x Unit Test Example
DESCRIPTION: A complete test case using Vert.x Unit to test an HTTP server verticle. It demonstrates the setup, deployment, and asynchronous testing patterns using the TestContext and Async objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/site/blog/posts/2016-01-18-using-hamcrest-matchers-with-vertx-unit.md#2025-04-19_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@RunWith(VertxUnitRunner.class)
public class MyFirstVerticleTest {

  private Vertx vertx;

  @Before
  public void setUp(TestContext context) {
    vertx = Vertx.vertx();
    vertx.deployVerticle(MyFirstVerticle.class.getName(),
      context.asyncAssertSuccess());
  }

  @Test
  public void test(TestContext context) {
    Async async = context.async();
    vertx.createHttpClient().get(8080, "localhost", "/")
      .handler(response -> {
        context.assertEquals(200, response.statusCode());
        response.bodyHandler(buffer -> {
          context.assertEquals("hello vert.x", buffer.toString("utf-8"));
          async.complete();
        });
      })
      .end();
  }
}
```

