TITLE: Reading Complete HTTP Response Body with Buffer in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates reading an entire HTTP response body by accumulating chunks into a buffer. This approach collects all data and processes it only after the complete response has been received.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web-site/blob/master/src/main/vertx2/docs_md/core_manual_ruby.md#2025-04-19_snippet_75

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
client = Vertx::HttpClient.new
client.host = 'foo.com'  

client.get_now('/some-path') do |resp|

  # Create a buffer to hold the entire response body
  body = Vertx::Buffer.create(0)

  resp.data_handler do |buffer|
    # Add chunk to the buffer
    body.append_buffer(buffer)
  end

  resp.end_handler do
    # The entire response body has been received
    puts "The total body received was #{body.length} bytes"
  end

end
```

